description.narrative: (Kenya): The long-term sustainability of USAID development assistance requires local ownership and strengthened capacity of local organizations and governments; strong local leadership; empowered communities with the ability to advocate for their needs; and systems in place that produce sustainable development outcomes at the national, county, sub-county, and community levels. Using FY 2019 funds, USAID will provide organizational development and capacity-building technical assistance to strengthen the role and capacity of local development organizations, local Kenyan entities, and local governments. This will foster locally led development and implementation of sustainable development programs in support of U.S. government priorities on supporting Kenya on its journey to self-reliance towards a time when foreign assistance will no longer be necessary. USAID support to Kenyan local private, public, and civil society sectors will help establish county-wide umbrella organizations that will draw on expertise and resources to foster community-led, -managed and -owned development. Through co-creation, USAID will work with these local entities to accelerate county-level self-reliance by identifying and addressing development priorities and challenges. The FY 2019 funds will also support the U.S. President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief and the Office of the U.S. Global AIDS Coordinator's mandate towards at least 70 percent of PEPFAR awards transitioned to local partners by September 2020. This activity also demonstrates unique American leadership and will help transition Kenya from an aid recipient country to an economic partner, a key goal under the Administration priorities and the State-USAID Joint Strategic Plan....
